################################################################################
# MVP 4 — RECRUITER DASHBOARD
# AI-Based Recruitment & Skill-Matching Platform
# Goal: Build the Recruiter workflow — job post management + candidate pipeline
# Reference: Image shows: Job Post, Add New Job Post, Filter, Shortlisted
################################################################################

## PHASE 1: Database Schema — Jobs & Recruiter
[ ] Create `recruiter_profiles` table:
    [ ] user_id (FK → users.id, unique)
    [ ] company_name (required)
    [ ] company_logo_url
    [ ] company_size (ENUM: 1-10, 11-50, 51-200, 201-1000, 1000+)
    [ ] industry
    [ ] company_website
    [ ] company_description
    [ ] location
    [ ] created_at, updated_at
[ ] Create `jobs` table:
    [ ] id (UUID)
    [ ] recruiter_id (FK → users.id)
    [ ] title (required)
    [ ] description (TEXT, required)
    [ ] required_skills (JSON array of strings)
    [ ] nice_to_have_skills (JSON array)
    [ ] location (string or 'Remote')
    [ ] job_type (ENUM: full-time, part-time, contract, internship, remote)
    [ ] experience_level (ENUM: entry, mid, senior, lead, executive)
    [ ] salary_min, salary_max (integer, monthly in INR)
    [ ] salary_currency (default: INR)
    [ ] is_salary_disclosed (boolean)
    [ ] openings_count (integer, default 1)
    [ ] application_deadline (date)
    [ ] status (ENUM: draft, active, paused, closed)
    [ ] views_count (integer, default 0)
    [ ] applications_count (integer, computed or tracked)
    [ ] created_at, updated_at
[ ] Run DB migrations for all new tables

## PHASE 2: Backend — Recruiter Profile APIs
[ ] GET /api/recruiter/profile → return recruiter's company profile
[ ] POST /api/recruiter/profile → create recruiter profile (one-time setup)
[ ] PUT /api/recruiter/profile → update company profile
[ ] PUT /api/recruiter/profile/logo → upload company logo (multipart)

## PHASE 3: Backend — Job Posting APIs
[ ] POST /api/recruiter/jobs → create new job posting
    [ ] Validate all required fields
    [ ] Status defaults to 'draft'
    [ ] Return created job
[ ] GET /api/recruiter/jobs → list all jobs posted by current recruiter
    [ ] Query params: status, page, limit, sort (newest, most_applications)
    [ ] Each item includes: title, status, applications_count, views_count, created_at
[ ] GET /api/recruiter/jobs/:id → get single job detail
[ ] PUT /api/recruiter/jobs/:id → update job details
[ ] PATCH /api/recruiter/jobs/:id/status → change status (activate, pause, close)
[ ] DELETE /api/recruiter/jobs/:id → delete draft job (cannot delete active/closed)
[ ] GET /api/recruiter/jobs/:id/analytics → job analytics:
    [ ] Total views, total applications, shortlisted count, avg match score

## PHASE 4: Backend — Candidate Pipeline APIs
[ ] GET /api/recruiter/jobs/:jobId/applicants → list all applicants for a job
    [ ] Include: candidate name, email, match score, application status, applied_at, resume link
    [ ] Query params: status, min_score, sort (match_score, applied_at), page, limit
[ ] GET /api/recruiter/jobs/:jobId/applicants/:applicationId → get single applicant detail:
    [ ] Candidate profile (name, contact, skills, experience, education)
    [ ] Resume download URL
    [ ] AI match score + detailed breakdown
    [ ] Application status + timeline
[ ] PATCH /api/recruiter/jobs/:jobId/applicants/:applicationId/status → update status:
    [ ] Valid transitions: applied → screening → shortlisted / rejected
    [ ] shortlisted → interview → offered / rejected
    [ ] Notify candidate via email on status change
[ ] POST /api/recruiter/jobs/:jobId/applicants/bulk-update → bulk update status:
    [ ] Accept array of application IDs + new status
    [ ] Useful for bulk shortlisting
[ ] GET /api/recruiter/shortlisted → all shortlisted candidates across all jobs
[ ] POST /api/recruiter/jobs/:jobId/applicants/:applicationId/notes → add recruiter note

